<h2><a href="http://www.debian.org/doc/debian-policy/" name="policy">
    Debian Policy Manual</a></h2>
<blockquote>
This manual describes the policy requirements for the Debian GNU/Linux
distribution. This includes the structure and contents of the Debian archive,
several design issues of the operating system, as well as technical
requirements that each package must satisfy to be included in the
distribution. 
<p>
<table>
<tr><td><strong>Authors:</strong>
<td>Ian Jackson and Christian Schwarz
<tr><td><strong>Maintainer:</strong>
<td valign="top">The Debian Policy Mailing List, 
    <a href="mailto:debian-policy@lists.debian.org">&lt;debian-policy@lists.debian.org&gt;</a>
<tr><td><strong>Status:</strong>
<td>ready
<tr><td><strong>Availability:</strong>
<td>Debian package <strong>debian-policy</strong>
<tr><td valign="top"><strong>Links:</strong>
<td>
   <a href="http://www.debian.org/doc/debian-policy/index.html">
     Release Version</a><br>
   <a href="http://www.debian.org/Bugs/db/pa/ldebian-policy.html">Proposed 
      amendments to Policy</a><br>
   You can also use <a href="cvs.html">CVS</a> to download the SGML
     source, with a <code>CVSROOT</code> based on
     <kbd>/cvs/debian-policy</kbd> and using the module
     <code>debian-policy</code>. 
</table>
</blockquote>
<p>

